            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When servicing vehicles with dual exhaust, order two (2) Accuseal double band clamps.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death when servicing the vehicle, park on a flat
                        level service, set the parking brake, turn the engine off and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury, allow the exhaust system to cool sufficiently before performing this
                        procedure.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the band clamp at the tail pipe to muffler joint. Separate the tail pipe from the
                    muffler and remove the clamp. Discard the clamp.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Before installing the Accuseal double band clamp, become familiar with its orientation.
                    Refer to Figure 1 and note the "Tail Pipe Side" is stamped for correct orientation.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0407021" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0350801.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="88px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Accuseal Double Band Clamp</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Tail Pipe Side of Clamp Stamped "PIPE"</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Muffler Side of Clamp is not Stamped</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the Accuseal double band clamp onto the tail pipe. Do not spread the clamp when
                    installing it or tighten the clamp at this time.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the tail pipe is fully inserted into the muffler stop position (Figure 2) and
                    slide the Accuseal double band clamp into position (Figure 3) between the tail pipe and muffler.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0407022" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0350802.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="288px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Assembly of Tail Pipe into Muffler Pipe</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Tail Pipe</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Accuseal Double Clamp</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Tail Pipe Must be Inserted to the Stop Position in the Muffler Pipe</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Stop Position</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. Muffler Pipe</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The muffler side of the double band clamp must be positioned at the edge of the muffler
                    pipe and must cover the slots of the muffler pipe (Figure 3).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0407023" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0350803.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Positioning Accuseal Double Clamp</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Tail Pipe</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Accuseal Double Clamp</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Muffler Pipe</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the clamp tightening system centered between two slots and avoid positioning
                    tightening system over a welded seam (Figure 4).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0407024" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0350804A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="168px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Top View of Clamp Positioned Around Muffler Slots</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Muffler Pipe Slot Positions</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Clamp Tightening System</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten both clamps to 27 to 37 Lbf-ft (37 to 50 Nm). Allow the clamp to rest for 5
                    minutes and retighten the clamps to specification.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
